28/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War crimes prosecutors announced on Tuesday (April 27th) that they have filed charges against Darko Jankovic for crimes against civilians committed during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict.
Jankovic, 38, allegedly tortured and killed at least 13 Bosniaks in May and June 1992 in the Zvornik municipality.
He was detained nearly a month ago.
(B92, Tanjug, RTS, Radio Free Europe - 27/04/10)
